    • Constructor Detail

      • TreeModel

        public TreeModel(TreeNode root,
                 boolean asksAllowsChildren,
                 Workspace workspace,
                 Observer... observers)
        This is the default constructor for the TreeModel
        This constructor sets the root of the JTree with a specified TreeNode
        Parameters:
        observers - an Observer which will be added to the root component if you don't want observer pass NULL
        root - an TreeNode is the root tree node that will be set as a root of the tree model.
        asksAllowsChildren - an boolean which indicates whether model root component allows children or not.
        workspace - an Workspace, if you want to set root node to be specific workspace, pass reference else pass NULL
        See Also:
        TreeNode, Workspace
